 165:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c **** /*
 166:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   Blocks the thread until a message arrives in the mailbox, but does
 167:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   not block the thread longer than "timeout" milliseconds (similar to
 168:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   the sys_arch_sem_wait() function). The "msg" argument is a result
 169:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   parameter that is set by the function (i.e., by doing "*msg =
 170:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   ptr"). The "msg" parameter maybe NULL to indicate that the message
 171:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   should be dropped.
 172:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c **** 
 173:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   The return values are the same as for the sys_arch_sem_wait() function:
 174:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   Number of milliseconds spent waiting or SYS_ARCH_TIMEOUT if there was a
 175:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   timeout.
 176:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c **** 
 177:Middlewares/Third_Party/LwIP/system/OS/sys_arch.c ****   Note that a function with a similar name, sys_mbox_fetch(), is
